Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of speeding. I acknowledge that my actions were irresponsible and put the safety of others at risk. I am deeply sorry for the danger I inflicted on those around me, and I take full responsibility for my actions.

I must admit that the thrill of driving my brand-new car got the best of me, and I wanted to see how fast it could go. However, I now realize that this was a grave error in judgment, and I deeply regret my decision.

Your Honor, I would like to bring to your attention that I did not initially receive the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) that was sent to me. This was purely due to my negligence in not checking my mail regularly. Had I been aware of the NIP's arrival, I assure you that I would have promptly responded to it and taken the appropriate actions.

I acknowledge that I am a young individual, only 26 years old, and I understand the importance of not only obeying traffic laws but also learning from my mistakes. While I do have penalty points on my license from previous speeding incidents, I would like to emphasize that this is the first time I have found myself facing criminal charges.

Furthermore, I would like to bring to your attention that I have been diagnosed with ADHD. While this does not justify or excuse my actions, it is a factor that may have influenced my impulsive behavior on that particular day. I am currently seeking treatment and taking necessary steps to manage my condition and ensure that such incidents do not recur.

I want to assure the court that I am genuinely remorseful for my actions and the potential harm I could have caused. I have taken this time to reflect on the consequences of my actions and have already begun making changes in my life to prevent any future offenses.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I acknowledge my guilt and express my deepest regret for the offense of speeding. I ask for your leniency and understanding, taking into consideration my young age, lack of prior criminal record, and the steps I am taking to address my ADHD. I am committed to learning from this experience and being a responsible member of society.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court.

