Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of speeding. I want to express my sincere remorse for my actions and the potential harm I could have caused to others. 

I understand the seriousness of my behavior and the consequences it may have had. I acknowledge that my decision to test the limits of my brand-new car was not only irresponsible but also highly dangerous. I am truly sorry for the danger I inflicted on those around me and take full responsibility for my actions.

I must also admit, Your Honor, that I did not initially receive the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) that was sent to me. Regrettably, I have a habit of neglecting to check my mail regularly, which resulted in me missing the important notice. I now understand the gravity of this negligence and the importance of promptly responding to legal proceedings. 

Furthermore, I would like to address my prior driving offenses mentioned in the input story. I acknowledge that I have penalty points on my license from three previous speeding incidents. However, it is important to note that these incidents do not reflect my overall character. Driving offenses aside, I have no record of criminal wrongdoing, and I take pride in being a law-abiding citizen.

Lastly, I wanted to mention that I have been diagnosed with ADHD, which may have contributed to my impulsive behavior on that particular day. While I understand that this does not excuse my actions, I am actively seeking treatment and working towards managing my condition. I am dedicated to taking the necessary steps to ensure that such incidents do not occur again in the future.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I accept full responsibility for my actions and express my deepest regret for the offense of speeding. I want to assure the court that I am genuinely remorseful and aware of the potential consequences of my actions. As an individual committed to obeying traffic laws and learning from my mistakes, I am devoted to becoming a better citizen. I am determined to be a responsible member of society and contribute positively to my community.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court.

